11 An Act relating to investment accounts; creating the
Oklahoma Dream Accounts Investment Program Act;
12 defining terms; creating the Oklahoma Dream Account
Investment Program; authorizing one-time
13 contributions to certain Trump Accounts; requiring
verification; making contributions subject to
14 availability of funds; prescribing order of
contributions; requiring the State Treasurer to
15 prescribe form; authorizing State Treasurer to
promulgate rules; providing construing provisions;
16 creating the Oklahoma Trump Account Investment Fund;
providing for deposits to fund; providing for
17 expenditures from fund; providing for
noncodification; providing for codification;
18 providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
19
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
23 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
24
HB4071 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma Dream
2 Accounts Investment Program Act".
3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9011.1 of Title 62, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. As used in this section:
7 1. "Trump Account" means a federally authorized Trump Account
8 established pursuant to 26 U.S.C., Section 530A;
9 2. "Eligible child" means a person who:
10 a. is under eighteen (18) years of age at the time the
11 application for a Trump Account is submitted,
12 b. is a citizen of the United States and is assigned a
13 valid Social Security number,
14 c. has a primary residence within this state, and
15 d. has an established Trump Account; and
16 3. "Program" means the Oklahoma Dream Account Investment
17 Program.
18 B. There is hereby created the Oklahoma Dream Account
19 Investment Program, to be administered by the State Treasurer.
20 C. The program shall authorize a one-time contribution by this
21 state into a Trump Account established for an eligible child,
22 subject to the availability of funds.
23 D. The State Treasurer is authorized to contribute to Trump
24 Accounts upon verification that the Trump Account is established for
HB4071 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 an e ligible child and that the contribution does not cause the
2 balance of the fund to exceed any applicable federal contribution
3 limitations. Upon verification, the State Treasurer shall make a
4 one-time deposit of Two Hundred Fifty Dollars ($250.00), as funds
5 become available in the Oklahoma Trump Account Investment Fund,
6 created pursuant to Section 3 of this act. The State Treasurer
7 shall make contributions, in the order that verified applications
8 are submitted.
9 E. Applications for the contribution shall be made on a form
10 prescribed by the State Treasurer. The State Treasurer may
11 promulgate rules to effectuate the provisions of this section.
12 F. Nothing in this act shall be construed to authorize a
13 contribution that is prohibited by federal laws or regulations.
14 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9011.2 of Title 62, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
18 for the State Treasurer to be designated the "Oklahoma Trump Account
19 Investment Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject
20 to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received
21 by the State Treasurer that are designated for deposit in the fund.
22 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
23 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the State Treasurer
24 for the purpose provided for in Section 2 of this act. Expenditures
HB4071 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 from the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State
2 Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with the
3 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
4 approval and payment.
5 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
6 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
7 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
8 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
9 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
10
